from typing import *   # --- py stmt 1
def f_gold(s: str) -> int:   # --- py stmt 2
    i = 0   # --- py stmt 3
    ans = 0   # --- py stmt 4
    chars = set()   # --- py stmt 5
    for j, c in enumerate(s):   # --- py stmt 6
        if c == ' ':   # --- py stmt 7
            continue   # --- py stmt 8
        elif c == '*':   # --- py stmt 9
            break   # --- py stmt 10
        while c in chars:   # --- py stmt 11
            chars.remove(s[i])   # --- py stmt 12
            i += 1   # --- py stmt 13
        chars.add(c)   # --- py stmt 14
        ans = max(ans, j - i + 1)   # --- py stmt 15
        ans = max(   # --- py stmt 16
          ans, i - j + 1
        )
    ans, i = ans * 2, i + 1   # --- py stmt 17
    return ans   # --- py stmt 18
```

def nlargest(n, iterable):   # --- py stmt 1
    if n == 1:   # --- py stmt 2
        it = iter(iterable)   # --- py stmt 3
        sentinel = object()   # --- py stmt 4
        result = max(it, default=sentinel)   # --- py stmt 5
        return [] if result is sentinel else [result]   # --- py stmt 6

    try:   # --- py stmt 7
        size = len(iterable)   # --- py stmt 8
    except (TypeError, AttributeError):   # --- py stmt 9
        pass   # --- py stmt 10
    else:   # --- py stmt 11
        if n >= size:   # --- py stmt 12
            return sorted(iterable, reverse=True)[:n]   # --- py stmt 13

    it = iter(iterable)   # --- py stmt 14
    result = [(elem, i) for i, elem in zip(range(0, -n, -1), it)]   # --- py stmt 15
    if not result:   # --- py stmt 16
        return result   # --- py stmt 17
    heapify(result)   # --- py stmt 18
    top = result[0][0]   # --- py stmt 19
    order = -n   # --- py stmt 20
    _heapreplace = heapreplace   # --- py stmt 21
    for elem in it:   # --- py stmt 22
        if top < elem:   # --- py stmt 23
            _heapreplace(result, (elem, order))   # --- py stmt 24
            top, _order = result[0]   # --- py stmt 25
            order -= 1   # --- py stmt 26
    result.sort(reverse=True)   # --- py stmt 27
    return [elem for (elem, order) in result]   # --- py stmt 28
```

function nlargest(n, iterable) {   // --- py stmt 1
    if (n === 1) {   // --- py stmt 2
        const it = iterable[Symbol.iterator]();   // --- py stmt 3
        const sentinel = {};   // --- py stmt 4
        const result = Math.max(...it, sentinel);   // --- py stmt 5
        return (result === sentinel) ? [] : [result];   // --- py stmt 6
    }

    let size;   // --- py stmt 7
    try {   // --- py stmt 7
        size = iterable.length;   // --- py stmt 8
    } catch (e) {}   // --- py stmt 9
    if (size !== undefined) {   // --- py stmt 11
        if (n >= size) {   // --- py stmt 12
            return iterable.sort((a, b) => b - a).slice(0, n);   // --- py stmt 13
        }
    }

    const it = iterable[Symbol.iterator]();   // --- py stmt 14
    const result = Array.from(it, (elem, i) => [elem, i]).slice(-n);   // --- py stmt 15
    if (!result.length) {   // --- py stmt 16
        return result;   // --- py stmt 17
    }
    heapify(result);   // --- py stmt 18
    let top = result[0][0];   // --- py stmt 19
    let order = -n;   // --- py stmt 20
    const _heapreplace = heapreplace;   // --- py stmt 21
    for (const elem of it) {   // --- py stmt 22
        if (top < elem) {   // --- py stmt 23
            _heapreplace(result, [elem, order]);   // --- py stmt 24
            [top, _order] = result[0];   // --- py stmt 25
            order -= 1;   // --- py stmt 26
        }
    }
    result.sort((a, b) => b[0] - a[0]);   // --- py stmt 27
    return result.map(([elem, order]) => elem);   // --- py stmt 28
}
